Program: Outlook
Title: 12/05/2011
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00gjc0x
Last Broadcast Date: Mon 16 May 2011
Extraordinary personal stories from around the world: today, an update from the Ivory Coast priest helping thousands of people who fled fighting after the disputed elections. Also the BBC's Zarghuna Kargar tells how her Afghan listeners gave her the courage to change her own life. Her book 'Dear Zari' is published by Chatto & Windus. And the eighty-six year old American dancer, who gives performances in her wheelchair! Show less